@wearedagger Spring/Summer 2027 collection, Lifestyles of the Bored and Disenfranchised, builds on the skate label's gritty foundations with an unexpected dose of romanticism. Inspired by founder Luke Rainey's working-class upbringing in Portrush, Northern Ireland, the collection imagines a rose-tinted version of youth, pairing distressed denim, graphic hoodies, board shorts, and customized Vans with softer tailoring and more elevated craftsmanship.⁠
⁠
The season also expands Dagger's ongoing collaborations with Apple and Vans. Models walked the runway with AirPods Max, took selfies on the catwalk, and wore heavily customized Vans slip-ons, reflecting the lived-in spirit that defines the brand. For Rainey, the collection is as much about healing as it is about clothes, reimagining the youth he never had into something joyful, hopeful, and beautifully imperfect.

@thenorthface.purplelabel is back with another quietly great collection. Guided by Nanamica founder Eiichiro Homma, the Japan-exclusive line continues to blur the line between outdoor gear and elevated everyday dressing, with FW26 delivering adaptable layering, updated double-knee pants, and standout pieces like a blocky checked field shirt and zip-in fleece cardigan.⁠
⁠
What really sets this collection apart is the styling. Rather than leaning into traditional techwear, its layered looks feel closer to Lemaire, AURALEE, and even LOEWE, proving once again that it's not just what you wear, but how you wear it.⁠

@orslow doesn't make much noise about its collaborations, but maybe it should. The Japanese label's latest with @saturdaysnyc is another reminder of why it's become a cult favorite: timeless Americana, woven and made in Japan, built with vintage shuttle looms, natural dyes, and, as the label itself puts it, "made for long affection."⁠
⁠
The capsule sticks to what orSlow does best, pairing a relaxed chambray work shirt with its signature military fatigue pants, while adding a subtle twist through aquamarine-dyed painter pants. Like its recent projects with @beams_official, @shopcanoeclub, and @evankinori, it's a quietly excellent collaboration that's almost too easy to miss.

